**Identifying the New Administrative Unit for "Xã An Ninh Tây, Huyện Tuy An, Tỉnh Phú Yên"**

Okay, let's break this down. The user's looking for the updated administrative unit given an old address. My primary task is to pinpoint the current administrative details for "Xã An Ninh Tây, Huyện Tuy An, Tỉnh Phú Yên".

First, the province. I know "Tỉnh Phú Yên" has undergone some changes.  A quick check of the relevant resolutions, specifically Resolution 60-NQ/TW, confirms that "Tỉnh Phú Yên" has been merged into "Tỉnh Đắk Lắk". This is key.

Now, let's focus on the ward.  I need to find what happened to "Xã An Ninh Tây". I'll scan the provided resolutions, looking for any mentions. Ah, here we go!  Resolution 1660/NQ-UBTVQH15, concerning the administrative reorganization of "Tỉnh Đắk Lắk", is the key.  Line 60 of this resolution indicates that "Xã An Ninh Tây" (along with An Ninh Đông and An Thạch) has been *merged* to form a new ward named "Xã Tuy An Đông". Bingo!

I also see another mention of "Xã An Ninh Tây" in relation to "Tỉnh Tây Ninh" in Resolution 1682/NQ-UBTVQH15. However, this is irrelevant since the starting province was Phú Yên, which is now part of Đắk Lắk. So, the Tây Ninh information can be disregarded.

To solidify my findings, I double-check the "New wards" data.  There, I can confirm that "Xã Tuy An Đông" indeed exists, with the correct province, Đắk Lắk. Its ward code is "22120".

Considering "Huyện Tuy An" in the old address, I am aware that districts are sometimes restructured when wards are changed. Since the resolution mentions merging wards under a new province, there isn't a direct mapping to new districts. "Huyện Tuy An" no longer exists as the wards "Xã An Ninh Tây" merged under "Tỉnh Đắk Lắk" to form "Xã Tuy An Đông".

So, based on all of this, my conclusion is clear: the new administrative unit for "Xã An Ninh Tây, Huyện Tuy An, Tỉnh Phú Yên" is "Xã Tuy An Đông", under "Tỉnh Đắk Lắk", with a confidence level that's incredibly high.
